medical-tutorial-name = Basic medicine
medical-tutorial-tooltip = Learn how to examine a patient, recognize simple injuries, and provide first aid.

medical-tut-welcome-bubble = This tutorial teaches you how to provide first aid.
medical-tut-welcome-chat = First we will check the patient's condition and choose simple treatments.
medical-tut-welcome-tts = Hello! This tutorial teaches you how to examine a patient and provide first aid.

medical-tut-find-patient-bubble = Find the patient and examine them with [tutkeybind="ExamineEntity"].
medical-tut-find-patient-chat = Start by examining the patient. First confirm who needs help, then check their condition.
medical-tut-find-patient-tts = Find the training patient and examine them. First we need to understand what happened.

medical-tut-take-analyzer-bubble = Pick up the highlighted health analyzer with [tutkeybind="UIClick"].
medical-tut-take-analyzer-chat = A health analyzer shows injuries, bleeding, and other important information. It is the first tool to take before treating someone.
medical-tut-take-analyzer-tts = Pick up the highlighted health analyzer. It will help you choose the right treatment.

medical-tut-scan-patient-bubble = Use the analyzer on the patient with [tutkeybind="UIClick"]. Wait for the scan to finish.
medical-tut-scan-patient-chat = Hold the analyzer and click the patient. The scan takes a moment, so do not walk away or put the device away. If you move far from the patient after scanning, return and scan them again: the analyzer does not update its data by itself.
medical-tut-scan-patient-tts = Scan the patient and wait for it to finish. If you move far away, return and scan the patient again.

medical-tut-explain-analyzer-patient-bubble = Start with the top part of the analyzer. It shows the patient's name, species, scan mode, and general condition.
medical-tut-explain-analyzer-patient-chat = Use this section to check who you are examining. The name and species help you identify the patient, while the status shows whether they are alive, critical, or dead. The result does not update by itself: if you move far from the patient, scan them again.
medical-tut-explain-analyzer-patient-tts = First look at the top section of the analyzer. It shows the patient's name, species, scan mode, and condition. If you move far away, return and scan the patient again.

medical-tut-explain-analyzer-vitals-bubble = The next section contains the body's basic indicators.
medical-tut-explain-analyzer-vitals-chat = Temperature shows overheating or hypothermia. Blood level helps you notice blood loss. Hunger and thirst show the body's general condition, but do not replace damage diagnostics.
medical-tut-explain-analyzer-vitals-tts = This section shows temperature, blood level, hunger, and thirst. These values help you assess the patient's general condition.

medical-tut-explain-analyzer-alerts-bubble = Pay attention to the warning section.
medical-tut-explain-analyzer-alerts-chat = A bleeding warning means that the patient is losing blood. Stop it as soon as possible. Other dangerous warnings may mean that the patient cannot be revived.
medical-tut-explain-analyzer-alerts-tts = Look for bleeding and other dangerous conditions in the warning section. Stop bleeding as soon as possible.

medical-tut-explain-analyzer-damage-bubble = Find the line with the total damage.
medical-tut-explain-analyzer-damage-chat = This is the sum of all damage on the patient. It helps you judge the severity of the condition, but does not tell you which treatment to use by itself.
medical-tut-explain-analyzer-damage-tts = Total damage shows how severe the patient's condition is. Check the details below to choose a treatment.

medical-tut-explain-analyzer-groups-bubble = The bottom section shows damage groups and damage types.
medical-tut-explain-analyzer-groups-chat = Damage is divided into physical injuries, burns, toxins, and suffocation. First identify the group, then check the specific damage type and amount. This helps you choose the right treatment.
medical-tut-explain-analyzer-groups-tts = The bottom section divides damage into groups and specific types. Use this information to choose the right treatment.

medical-tut-take-gauze-bubble = Pick up the highlighted gauze with [tutkeybind="UIClick"]. Switch to your free hand if needed.
medical-tut-take-gauze-chat = Pick up the gauze with your free hand. You can keep the analyzer in your other hand.
medical-tut-take-gauze-tts = Pick up the highlighted gauze. Switch to your free hand if needed.

medical-tut-apply-gauze-bubble = Apply the gauze to the patient with [tutkeybind="UIClick"]. Wait for the procedure to finish.
medical-tut-apply-gauze-chat = Hold the gauze and use it on the patient. It stops bleeding and helps with cuts.
medical-tut-apply-gauze-tts = Apply the gauze to the patient and wait for the procedure to finish.

medical-tut-take-brutepack-bubble = Now pick up the highlighted trauma pack with [tutkeybind="UIClick"].
medical-tut-take-brutepack-chat = Pick up the trauma pack with your free hand. You can keep the analyzer in your other hand.
medical-tut-take-brutepack-tts = Now pick up the highlighted trauma pack.

medical-tut-apply-brutepack-bubble = Apply the trauma pack to the patient with [tutkeybind="UIClick"]. Wait for the procedure to finish.
medical-tut-apply-brutepack-chat = Use the trauma pack on the patient. It treats injuries from impacts.
medical-tut-apply-brutepack-tts = Apply the trauma pack to the patient and wait for the procedure to finish.

medical-tut-take-ointment-bubble = Pick up the highlighted ointment with [tutkeybind="UIClick"].
medical-tut-take-ointment-chat = Ointment treats burns on the outside of the body. It does not replace treatment for bruises or bleeding.
medical-tut-take-ointment-tts = Pick up the highlighted ointment. It is used to treat burns.

medical-tut-apply-ointment-bubble = Apply the ointment to the patient with [tutkeybind="UIClick"] and wait for it to finish.
medical-tut-apply-ointment-chat = Use the ointment on the patient like the previous treatment. Treatment takes time, so do not move or put the ointment away.
medical-tut-apply-ointment-tts = Apply the ointment to the patient and wait for it to finish.

medical-tut-self-care-intro-bubble = Now let us see how to provide first aid to yourself.
medical-tut-self-care-intro-chat = If you are injured, watch the health alerts. They show what is happening to your character and what treatment may be needed.
medical-tut-self-care-intro-tts = Now let us see how to provide first aid to yourself. Watch the health alerts: they show what is happening to your character.

medical-tut-take-self-ointment-bubble = Now try helping yourself. Pick up the second highlighted ointment with [tutkeybind="UIClick"].
medical-tut-take-self-ointment-chat = Sometimes you are the one who needs help. You received a small training burn. Pick up the second ointment and use it on yourself.
medical-tut-take-self-ointment-tts = Sometimes you are the one who needs help. Pick up the second highlighted ointment.

medical-tut-apply-self-ointment-bubble = Use the ointment on yourself with [tutkeybind="UIClick"] and wait for it to finish.
medical-tut-apply-self-ointment-chat = Healing yourself works the same way as healing someone else. Use the ointment on yourself and stay still until it finishes.
medical-tut-apply-self-ointment-tts = Use the ointment on yourself and wait for it to finish. Do not move during the procedure.

medical-tut-finish-bubble = First aid is complete.
medical-tut-finish-chat = Simple injuries can be treated by anyone. Complex chemicals, surgery, severe trauma, and unknown symptoms belong to a doctor. Do not experiment on a patient if you do not know what you are doing.
medical-tut-finish-tts = You can now provide simple first aid. Complex chemicals and surgery require a doctor. Do not experiment without training.

medical-tut-softlock-keep-gauze = Do not drop the gauze: use it on the patient first.
medical-tut-softlock-keep-brutepack = Do not put away the trauma pack: use it on the patient first.
medical-tut-softlock-keep-ointment = Do not put away the ointment: use it on the patient first.
medical-tut-softlock-keep-self-ointment = Do not put away the ointment: use it on yourself first.
medical-tut-softlock-open-analyzer = Pick up the health analyzer first. Its interface will be needed in the next step.
